dcMetadata.abstract_tsi: Digitization note: Due to its large size, this item was scanned in sections, stitched together, and edited.; Finished map showing the upper St. Lawrence River.; Dotted lines indicate the routes of General Jeffery Amherst's army from Oswego to Montréal in 1760 and Robert Rogers's route from Montréal to Niagara in 1760.; Signed in second cartouche: T. Davies lt R Artillery 1760.; Shows siege batteries and bombardment of Fort Lévis in August 1760.
